# UI Design System Guide â€” Operator Panel
### How the Package Module was redesigned â€” and how to apply it to other modules

---

## 1. Design Philosophy

The goal was to move from a **functional-but-plain** interface to a **premium product feel** â€” the kind of UI that makes an operator feel they are using a well-crafted SaaS tool, not a generic form page.

The three pillars used for every decision:

| Pillar | What it means in practice |
|---|---|
| **Depth** | Cards should feel like they are floating. Use shadows, borders, and subtle gradients. |
| **Hierarchy** | The most important element on the page must visually dominate. Titles, CTAs, and status indicators all have distinct visual weight. |
| **Feedback** | Every interactive element must respond â€” hover, active, disabled states are never left blank. |

